The paper deals with vision-language tasks and proposes a method to improve the performance of state-of-the-art models by adding weak supervision for alignment between visual objects and words. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves training models using cross-entropy loss, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and also discusses attention distributions, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
